{"text": "at the barrier. We shall use this result in order to get an expression for the Rabi frequency \u03a9of oscillations in a\n\ndouble well system.\n\n207\n\n====== [43.2] An exact solution - the eigenstates\n\nThe unperturbed basis is 0\u27e9, k\u27e9with energies \u03b50 and \u03b5k. The level spacing of the quasi continuum states is \u2206. The\n\ncouplings between the discrete state and the quasi-continuum levels are \u03c3k. The set of equations for the eigenstates En\u27e9is\n\n\u03b50\u03a80 +\n\nX\n\nk\u2032\n\n\u03c3k\u2032\u03a8k\u2032 = E\u03a80\n\n(43.6)\n\n\u03b5k\u03a8k + \u03c3k\u03a80 = E\u03a8k,\n\nk = 1, 2, 3, ...\n\n(43.7)\n\nFrom the kth equation we deduce that\n\n\u03a8k\n\n=\n\n\u03c3k\n\nE \u2212\u03b5k\n\n\u03a80\n\n(43.8)\n\nHence the expression for the eigenstates is \u03a8\u27e9\n\n=\n\n\u221ap 0\u27e9+ \u221ap\n\nX\n\nk\n\n\u03c3k\n\nE \u2212\u03b5k k\u27e9\n\n(43.9)\n\nwhere p \u2261 \u03a80 2 is determined by normalization. Substitution of \u03a8k into the 0th equation leads to the secular equation\n\nfor the eigenenergies\n\nX\n\nk\n\n\u03c32\n\nk\n\nE \u2212\u03b5k\n\n=\n\nE \u2212\u03b50\n\n(43.10)\n\nThis equation can be illustrated graphically. Clearly the roots En interlace the the unperturbed values \u03b5k. For equal\n\nspacing \u2206and equal couplings \u03c3 the secular equation can be written as\n\ncot\n\n\u0012\n\n\u03c0 E\n\n\u2206\n\n\u0013\n\n= 1\n\n\u03c0\n\n\u2206\n\n\u03c32 (E \u2212\u03b50)\n\n;\n\nEn =\n\n\u0012\n\nn + 1\n\n\u03c0 \u03c6n\n\n\u0013\n\n\u2206\n\n(43.11)\n\nwhere \u03c6 changes monotonically from \u03c0 to 0. Above and below we use the following identities:\n\n\u221e\n\nX\n\nn=\u2212\u221e\n\n1\n\nx \u2212\u03c0n = cot(x) \u2261S,\n\n\u221e\n\nX\n\nn=\u2212\u221e\n\n1\n\n(x \u2212\u03c0n)2 =\n\n1\n\nsin2(x) = 1 + S2\n\n(43.12)\n\nUsing the second identity and the secular equation one obtains a compact expression for the normalization constant\n\np\n\n= \u03a80 2\n\n= \u27e80 En\u27e9 2\n\n=\n\n\u03c32\n\n(En \u2212\u03b50)2 + (\u0393/2)2\n\n(43.13)\n\nwhere\n\n\u0393\n\n2\n\n=\n\nr\n\n\u03c32 +\n\n\u0010 \u03c0\n\n\u2206\u03c32\n\n\u00112\n\n(43.14)\n\nThe plot of \u03a80 2 versus En is the Wigner Lorentzian. It gives the overlap of the eigenstates with the unperturbed\n\ndiscrete state.\n\n208\n\n====== [43.3] An exact solution - the time dependent decay\n\nWe switch to the interaction picture:\n\n\u03a8k(t)\n\n=\n\nck(t)e\u2212i\u03b5kt,\n\nk = 0, 1, 2, 3, ...\n\n(43.15)\n\nWe distinguish between ck and c0.", "embedding": [-0.0031907703, 0.00012657332, 0.031038517, -0.017838202, -0.035067137, -0.026051685, -0.041047785, 0.026963213, -0.0696528, 0.091210805, 0.023216367, 0.011861146, -0.020478604, -0.049568433, -0.019994954, 0.022695087, -0.017957117, -0.013221509, -0.061333675, 0.025809422, 0.029677985, 0.008153884, -0.07436922, -0.01315769, -0.035529274, 0.04176785, 0.013648419, 0.02764593, 0.046946276, 0.064148314, 0.05125398, -0.010449671, 0.03388284, -0.04911498, -0.0011972176, 0.014116691, 0.024391387, -0.04748918, 0.033742487, -0.027589712, 0.03339915, 0.0036882213, -0.030410819, -0.024994282, -0.026175927, -0.020700138, -0.06031213, 0.013447802, -0.005348618, -0.06747702, -0.012982678, -0.020226818, 0.044832036, -0.020738112, -0.0031698155, 0.024297759, 0.025143608, -0.010357646, -0.008759927, 0.02283291, 0.045570657, 0.0037571874, 0.03655048, -0.03342678, -0.00043947698, 0.041678652, -0.014285985, 0.05742401, -0.0056104837, -0.028717382, 0.016489767, -0.0105258785, -0.007768308, 0.010139947, -0.040806778, 0.051517077, -0.0025938519, -0.059194647, -0.042983893, 0.023129001, -0.0052018003, -0.004324085, 8.139474e-05, 0.013475262, -0.017837683, -0.002354854, -0.012771706, -0.016983388, 0.020432435, 0.0081114825, 0.037875723, 0.06081807, -0.01148741, 0.017048921, 0.023667414, 0.025892368, -0.012508489, 0.0046097995, 0.05299147, 0.037920326, -0.009512853, 0.03884134, -0.012196886, 0.0529162, -0.010405619, 0.0596031, 0.004609335, 0.05960735, 0.02701726,